<br>
You can wear the solstice earring before 51, it will have reduced stats, at 31 its probably on par with an elec/BS earring.<br>
<br>
White lotus pants would be rather hard to attain mostly due to faction.  Having a seb berserker cloak and a spiked seahorse belt is silly, you could get a better cloak (heiro) since you dont need the haste effect, and it would be cheaper.  Epic at 31, possible, but is it worth the effort on a lvl 31?  Tynn shackle? same thing, possible, but is it worth the effort at that lvl? Personally I waited for 47 (when my monk could solo the mobs for the last shackle) to complete that quest, as doing it before then seemed silly at best.<br>
<br>
As far as Tstaff weighing you down, who cares? At that lvl the difference is minor when you are that insanely twinked, and its still an insane weapon.  Mine brings me to 21 wt (out of 17 allowed), and I still use it over my FoI/SoS combo, it simply does more dmg, I end fights faster, and have more life left at the end, lower ac or not.<br>
<br>
However, if you are set on getting below your wt limit for the time being, sell the SBC, get a heiro, and get some lighter 1h weaps or a IFS until you are high enough for the tstaff to proc, at which point you should find it to be superior whether or not it makes you overweight. <p> <center><img src=http://www.webspawner.com/users/ceri2/cerisig.jpg><BR><font size="1"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=86991">Arianwen Taur`amandil  53 Druid and Tradeskill Diva</a><BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=14796">Ceridwen al`Ban  60 High Priestess</a><BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=323015">Geckonia Chazaliae  47 Lizzy Monk</a><BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=87181">Wenlan Rainjarbot  60 Warder</a></font><BR>
